text: The is a limited express train service in Japan operated by Kyushu Railway Company (JR Kyushu), which runs between and . ==Rolling stock== ===Present=== * KiHa 185 series DMU: 1992-Present ===Past=== * KiHa 58/65 DMU File:JRkyusyu kiha 58 703 kumagawa tsubaki kyusyuexpcollar.jpg|KiHa 58 Kumagawa in 1992 File:JRkyusyu kiha 65 kumagawa tsubaki kyusyuexpcollar.jpg|KiHa 65 Kumagawa in 1992 ==History== The Kumagawa was first introduced from 1 April 1959 as a semi-express service between and . From 5 March 1966, the train was upgraded to become an express service. ==References== Category:Named passenger trains of Japan Category:Railway services introduced in 1959
